# New feature checklist

Run through this when starting (or finishing) a feature that touches more than one layer of the stack.

## Plan first
- [ ] One-sentence summary of what we're building
- [ ] Key decisions / trade-offs documented
- [ ] File tree drafted before any code

## Data layer
- [ ] Schema change (if any) added and migrated
- [ ] Types re-exported from the schema (no manual duplication)
- [ ] Query scoped by `user_id` (or equivalent ownership column)
- [ ] RLS / DB-level policy in place if applicable

## API / server action layer
- [ ] Session check at the top
- [ ] Zod parse on all input
- [ ] Returns `{ data, error }` (or appropriate HTTP status for a route handler)
- [ ] No secrets leak into the response

## Frontend layer
- [ ] Server Component by default; `"use client"` only where required
- [ ] Loading and error states handled
- [ ] Optimistic update or revalidation strategy decided
- [ ] Accessibility: keyboard nav + ARIA where needed

## Tests & tooling
- [ ] At least one happy-path test and one auth-failure test
- [ ] `pnpm lint` clean (see `09-tooling-feedback`)
- [ ] `pnpm typecheck` clean
- [ ] Commits cleanly (pre-commit hook passes)
